# 07 Retention, Deletion, and Backups

## Intent
Enforce minimal default retention and reliable end-to-end deletion.

## Mandatory
- Assign retention class to every dataset.
- Use minimal default retention; extensions require documented justification.
- Implement automatic expiry/deletion jobs with observability.
- Support verified erasure workflows across primary stores, replicas, caches, and backups.

## Operational Rules
- Backups must be encrypted and mapped to deletion propagation policy.
- Deletion requests must generate verifiable completion evidence.

## Release Blockers
- Data classes without retention policy.
- No tested deletion orchestration path.
